      "role": "user",
      "content": "\"necessary component\" and \"stable backbone\" sounds pretty definitive. but if people keep arguing against it because of the waste and safety stuff, aren't they basically just making it harder to solve the climate crisis? like, can we even afford to ignore nuclear anymore?",
